0
00:00:27,494 --> 00:00:29,394
[Man Narrating ]
There was a time...

1
00:00:29,496 --> 00:00:32,021
when the world was made of dreams.

2
00:00:32,132 --> 00:00:33,861
All living creatures of the ocean...

3
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:36,663
Iived happily in peace.

4
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:39,433
The main purpose of their lives...

5
00:00:39,539 --> 00:00:42,508
was to follow the voice of their hearts.

6
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:47,205
Nobody knows for certain
when everything started to change...

7
00:00:47,313 --> 00:00:50,976
when rules emerged that made them
forget their inner voices.

8
00:00:52,318 --> 00:00:55,947
And one day, without even noticing it...

9
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:59,423
the creatures of the oceans
stopped dreaming.

10
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:05,058
They were always busy-
fishing day and night...

11
00:01:05,165 --> 00:01:08,032
treasuring their material possessions.

12
00:01:08,134 --> 00:01:12,833
Instead of fishing to live,
they now lived to fish.

13
00:01:12,939 --> 00:01:17,967
But among them, there was one
born destined to change it all...

14
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:21,206
one who had never listened
to the voice of the crowds...

15
00:01:21,314 --> 00:01:23,407
but to the voice of his heart.

16
00:01:24,451 --> 00:01:26,976
One who still had a dream...

17
00:01:27,087 --> 00:01:29,214
and was willing to test his courage-

18
00:01:29,322 --> 00:01:31,586
even risking his life-

19
00:01:31,691 --> 00:01:35,491
to rediscover the true purpose
of his life...

20
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:37,620
and, without knowing it...

21
00:01:37,730 --> 00:01:42,133
open the world of dreams
for all other creatures.

22
00:01:42,235 --> 00:01:45,170
This is his story..

23
00:01:51,311 --> 00:01:52,778
[ Gasps ]

24
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:55,939
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

25
00:01:59,052 --> 00:02:00,519
[ Gasps ]

26
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:07,126
- [ Growls ]
- [ Gasps ]

27
00:02:07,227 --> 00:02:09,058
[ Whimpering ]

28
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:12,357
[ Whimpering ]

29
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:14,490
- Daniel, wake up!
- The wave!

30
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:17,502
- Dreaming about the wave again?
- Yes.

31
00:02:17,604 --> 00:02:21,131
Well, forget about your wave.
Come on, let's go fish. We're already late.

32
00:02:21,241 --> 00:02:22,640
[ Sighs ]

33
00:02:25,245 --> 00:02:27,577
I still don't get this stuff
about fishing all day.

34
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,739
We already have enough
fish in the lagoon...

35
00:02:29,849 --> 00:02:32,511
to feed ourselves for the rest
of our entire lives.

36
00:02:32,619 --> 00:02:35,986
Ah, don't start with that again.
You know the rules.

37
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:37,784
Yeah, yeah.

38
00:02:37,891 --> 00:02:41,793
"You can't go surfing
because it's a waste of time."

39
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:44,329
"You can't leave the lagoon
because it's too dangerous."

40
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:47,331
Blah, blah, fishing, fishing
and more fishing.

41
00:02:47,433 --> 00:02:49,924
- I'm sick and tired-
- Hi, Daniel! Hi, Michael! Hi, Daniel!

42
00:02:50,036 --> 00:02:53,096
Guess what I saw today.
You won't believe it. You won't believe it.

43
00:02:53,206 --> 00:02:55,640
It was a starfish as big as a mountain.

44
00:02:55,742 --> 00:02:57,642
It was so huge.

45
00:02:57,744 --> 00:03:00,008
It was giant! It was enormous!

46
00:03:00,113 --> 00:03:02,308
It was ginormous!

47
00:03:02,415 --> 00:03:06,374
- [ Michael, Scoffing ] A giant starfish?
- Don't be mean.

48
00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:09,421
Yeah. Anyway, it was supergigantic...

49
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:11,683
all orange and bright.

50
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:15,022
It was so incredible.
Can you believe it? Can you believe it?

51
00:03:15,128 --> 00:03:16,823
As big as a mountain!

52
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:18,898
Ooh. Incredible.

53
00:03:18,998 --> 00:03:21,558
- And guess what.
- What, little guy?

54
00:03:21,668 --> 00:03:24,034
That star is mine, mine and only mine.

55
00:03:24,137 --> 00:03:26,196
Don't touch it. Don't touch it.

56
00:03:26,306 --> 00:03:28,866
I'm watching you.
I'm watching you. I'm watching you.

57
00:03:28,975 --> 00:03:31,535
[ Laughs ]
Don't worry, Sparky.

58
00:03:31,644 --> 00:03:33,976
The huge starfish is yours
and nobody else's.

59
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:37,049
Yes! I love it! And it's mine.

60
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:40,415
Because when I saw it,
it was supergigantic!

61
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,250
Yes! I love it. I love it. And it's mine.

62
00:03:43,356 --> 00:03:47,417
That's good, Sparky. Now go play
and dream with your giant starfish.

63
00:03:47,527 --> 00:03:50,792
Dream? Yeah! Yeah!
Talking about dreams, I feel sleepy.

64
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:53,365
'Cause I didn't sleep well last night
because of my starfish.

65
00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:55,730
Starfish. That's right.
Sparky's giant starfish.

66
00:03:55,835 --> 00:03:57,735
Yes! Because it's mine
and only mine!

67
00:03:57,837 --> 00:04:00,829
Yeah. Yeah, I feel sleepy.
[ Exhales ]

68
00:04:00,940 --> 00:04:03,033
[ Sighs, Snoring ]

69
00:04:03,142 --> 00:04:05,406
[ Daniel Chuckling ]

70
00:04:05,511 --> 00:04:07,536
[ Snoring ]

71
00:04:09,382 --> 00:04:12,510
- Hey, we have to put Sparky to bed.
- What about fishing?

72
00:04:12,619 --> 00:04:15,247
Shh. Don't complain. Come and help me.

73
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:22,394
[ Sighs ]
That Sparky's such a pest.

74
00:04:22,495 --> 00:04:25,225
- Well, you're so slow.
- Slow?

75
00:04:25,331 --> 00:04:27,231
Bet you can't catch me!

76
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:29,858
No fair! You got an early start.

77
00:04:29,969 --> 00:04:32,631
- [ Laughing ] You snooze, you lose.
- I'm right on your tail!

78
00:04:32,739 --> 00:04:35,606
[ Both Laughing, Exclaiming ]

79
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:37,676
[ Michael ]
Watch this move!

80
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,745
[ Daniel ]
Nice! [ Laughs ]

81
00:04:41,347 --> 00:04:43,941
[ Michael ]
Hey, I taught you everything you know.

82
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:47,349
- Who's the master now? Whoa! [ Panting ]
- Yeah, not for long.

83
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:49,421
You're never gonna catch me, man!

84
00:04:49,522 --> 00:04:52,116
[ Both Panting, Exclaiming ]

85
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:55,820
- [ Michael ] Hey! Hey, look out for the rock!
- Whoa!

86
00:04:55,928 --> 00:04:57,452
[ Laughing ]

87
00:04:59,365 --> 00:05:01,265
[ Daniel ]
Look out, little fishies!

88
00:05:12,936 --> 00:05:20,628
<font face="Algerian" color="WHITE">THE DOLPHIN
STORY OF A DREAMER
<<<<<<Subs By SIVACHERRY>>>>>></font>

89
00:05:21,554 --> 00:05:23,522
- [ Laughing ]
- Whoa!

90
00:05:23,623 --> 00:05:26,091
[ Both Panting, Exclaiming ]

91
00:05:28,428 --> 00:05:30,862
- Daniel, wait.
- [ Exclaims ]

92
00:05:30,963 --> 00:05:32,453
[ Laughs ]

93
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:43,070
Ah! See?

94
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:44,643
You can't catch me.

95
00:05:44,744 --> 00:05:47,338
What happened? Come on, jump.

96
00:05:47,447 --> 00:05:50,610
- No way I'm doing that.
- Ooh.

97
00:05:50,717 --> 00:05:54,813
You remind me of an animal
that goes buk, buk, buk, buk!

98
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:57,287
Chicken.
[ Laughing ]

99
00:05:57,390 --> 00:06:00,553
I'm not playing anymore, Daniel.
You're cheating.

100
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:02,992
- You know we're not allowed
to leave the lagoon.
- I know.

101
00:06:03,096 --> 00:06:06,554
We're not allowed to leave the lagoon.
Ah. Come on, Michael.

102
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,964
You and I both know
the waves look great today.

103
00:06:09,068 --> 00:06:11,764
- Mm-mmm.
- [ Sighs ]

104
00:06:13,239 --> 00:06:15,070
Show-off.

105
00:06:17,643 --> 00:06:19,577
[ Exclaiming ]

106
00:06:19,679 --> 00:06:23,410
Whoa! This is, like,
the best wave I've ever seen.

107
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,923
Oh! She's amazing.

108
00:06:36,028 --> 00:06:37,518
I wish Michael could see this.

109
00:06:42,969 --> 00:06:45,767
Whoa-ho-ho-ho!

110
00:06:49,509 --> 00:06:51,841
Ahh!
[ Gasps ]

111
00:06:52,845 --> 00:06:54,904
Uh, good morning, Leader.

112
00:06:55,014 --> 00:06:57,744
We were chasing each other,
and we were going so fast...

113
00:06:57,850 --> 00:07:00,250
I couldn't stop,
so I had no option but to jump.

114
00:07:00,353 --> 00:07:03,288
Uh-huh. Just playing, right?

115
00:07:03,389 --> 00:07:07,917
And you had no option
but to jump... and surf a wave.

116
00:07:08,027 --> 00:07:09,927
Mm-hmm. Exactly.

117
00:07:10,029 --> 00:07:13,123
If not, I would've smashed myself
against the sharp rocks and coral.

118
00:07:13,232 --> 00:07:15,632
And that's no good. Right?

119
00:07:15,735 --> 00:07:18,602
Seems to me that something's wrong
with your sonar system, boy.

120
00:07:18,704 --> 00:07:21,070
Oh. Yes, yes.

121
00:07:21,174 --> 00:07:23,870
I mean- No, no! Everything's fine.

122
00:07:23,976 --> 00:07:26,103
I guess I just didn't think about it.

123
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:29,807
Then I think I need
to refresh your memory a little bit.

124
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:31,383
Follow me.

125
00:07:38,491 --> 00:07:40,550
I really can't understand you.

126
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:42,594
We're almost finished
with class, but, no...

127
00:07:42,695 --> 00:07:45,789
Daniel has to put
a jellyfish on for a hat.

128
00:07:45,898 --> 00:07:48,423
Daniel has to juggle sea cucumbers.

129
00:07:48,534 --> 00:07:50,058
[ Sighs ]

130
00:07:50,169 --> 00:07:54,105
[ Female Voice ]
Daniel. Daniel, come.

131
00:07:54,207 --> 00:07:56,971
- Michael, look!
- What?

132
00:07:57,076 --> 00:07:59,374
- Did you see that?
- Huh?

133
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,913
- You can't wait forever, Daniel.
- [ Gasps ]

134
00:08:02,014 --> 00:08:03,743
You have a mission to accomplish.

135
00:08:03,850 --> 00:08:07,081
The sun is already moving
into its position.

136
00:08:07,186 --> 00:08:11,145
- A mission?
- Dream... or don 't dream.

137
00:08:11,257 --> 00:08:14,954
Come... or don 't.

138
00:08:15,061 --> 00:08:18,497
You may wait, but the ocean won 't.

139
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:22,531
- Did you hear that?
- What?

140
00:08:22,635 --> 00:08:24,660
- That voice.
- [ Gasps ]

141
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:26,829
There! There, Daniel!

142
00:08:39,986 --> 00:08:43,478
- Did you see those markings on its belly?
- It got into the lagoon!

143
00:08:43,589 --> 00:08:45,489
- Let's go!
- Yeah!

144
00:09:05,578 --> 00:09:08,547
[ Dolphins Whispering, Murmuring ]

145
00:09:24,964 --> 00:09:27,262
Listen to me. You're safe.

146
00:09:27,366 --> 00:09:29,766
It's a manta. It's harmless.
Just don 't get too close.

147
00:09:29,869 --> 00:09:31,894
What do we do?

148
00:09:32,004 --> 00:09:34,336
Nothing.
At least, not at the time being.

149
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:37,000
She's beautiful.

150
00:09:37,109 --> 00:09:40,772
That thing came in from the outside,
from the ocean. I just know it's dangerous.

151
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:43,815
I love it! It's just like
my giant starfish!

152
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:47,818
Yes, it is! It's mine, mine!
I saw it first, and I will call it Jumpy.

153
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:51,117
Yes! Because it looks like me,
like in my dream.

154
00:09:51,223 --> 00:09:53,623
Dream?
[ Sighs ]

155
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:55,694
[ Snoring ]

156
00:09:56,963 --> 00:09:58,897
[ Gasps ]
Hey, Daniel.

157
00:09:58,998 --> 00:10:01,125
Don't get too close.

158
00:10:04,337 --> 00:10:06,931
Hi. I'm Daniel.

159
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:08,734
I know.

160
00:10:08,841 --> 00:10:11,275
You're Daniel Alexander Dolphin.

161
00:10:11,377 --> 00:10:13,868
- Huh?
- You've got the glow.

162
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:18,076
The glow? What glow?

163
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:20,652
You have got the glow of a dreamer.

164
00:10:20,753 --> 00:10:24,211
Was it you who was talking to me earlier-
outside the reef?

165
00:10:24,323 --> 00:10:28,589
- No, Daniel. I am just a messenger.
- [ Sparky Snoring ]

166
00:10:28,694 --> 00:10:32,687
I have come to tell you
that the sun is almost in the right place.

167
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:37,761
If you want to find the wave of your dream,
you have to leave.

168
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:40,498
Daniel Alexander Dolphin!

169
00:10:40,606 --> 00:10:43,939
You get back with the others
in the group. Now!

170
00:10:44,043 --> 00:10:45,977
I only want to talk to her.

171
00:10:46,078 --> 00:10:48,103
Are you disobeying me,
Daniel Alexander?

172
00:10:48,214 --> 00:10:49,772
But, Leader, she's harmless.

173
00:10:49,882 --> 00:10:52,646
Daniel, go back. Now!

174
00:10:52,752 --> 00:10:55,949
- [ All Gasping ]
- [ Ocean Roaring ]

175
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:59,324
[ Gasps ]
What's happening?

176
00:10:59,425 --> 00:11:01,791
Don't be afraid, Daniel.

177
00:11:01,894 --> 00:11:03,657
- Only you can hear me.
- Why?

178
00:11:03,763 --> 00:11:07,130
Because the rest of your pod
doesn't dream anymore.

179
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:11,829
However, Daniel, you never stopped
believing in your dreams.

180
00:11:11,937 --> 00:11:13,837
Many made fun of you...

181
00:11:13,939 --> 00:11:16,305
and many will continue doing it.

182
00:11:16,409 --> 00:11:19,970
Sometimes that's the price you have to
pay for not being understood...

183
00:11:20,079 --> 00:11:22,639
for being different from the rest.

184
00:11:22,748 --> 00:11:25,342
But never stop being you.

185
00:11:25,451 --> 00:11:28,750
Never let your fears
stand in the way of your dreams.

186
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:30,344
Never.

187
00:11:31,724 --> 00:11:33,658
Now I must go.

188
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:35,784
No. Please don't leave yet.

189
00:11:35,895 --> 00:11:37,886
There are so many things
I want to ask you.

190
00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:41,330
Always listen to the voice
of your heart, Daniel...

191
00:11:41,434 --> 00:11:44,801
no matter what others
might think or say.

192
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:46,804
- [ Snoring ]
- If you do it...

193
00:11:46,906 --> 00:11:49,374
maybe someday
you will find your truth...

194
00:11:49,475 --> 00:11:54,037
if you are strong and brave enough
to follow your dreams.

195
00:11:54,146 --> 00:11:57,604
- Will I ever see you again?
- I'm not sure.

196
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:59,947
But I have fulfilled my mission.

197
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:05,354
If you follow your dreams,
you will never feel lonely again, Daniel.

198
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:06,925
Never.

199
00:12:12,798 --> 00:12:15,266
[ Narrator]
And so Daniel discovered...

200
00:12:15,367 --> 00:12:18,268
that as long as he followed
the dictates of his heart...

201
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:21,669
he would never feel lonely again.

202
00:12:21,774 --> 00:12:23,241
Never.

203
00:12:31,884 --> 00:12:33,351
[ Sighs ]

204
00:12:42,461 --> 00:12:44,929
[ Peaceful Snuffling ]

205
00:12:51,837 --> 00:12:54,305
- Everything okay?
- Yes.

206
00:12:54,406 --> 00:12:57,603
Good. I was worried about
what that manta might do.

207
00:12:57,710 --> 00:13:00,338
Don't you worry.
Everything's quiet.

208
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:03,540
But I don't like creatures
that come from outside of the reef.

209
00:13:03,649 --> 00:13:05,617
Yes, I know.

210
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:08,278
Actually, I'm a little worried too.

211
00:13:08,387 --> 00:13:12,255
Especially about that manta.
I've heard of that one.

212
00:13:12,358 --> 00:13:14,326
She's the one with
the markings on her belly.

213
00:13:14,426 --> 00:13:16,553
But, Leader, is she dangerous?

214
00:13:16,662 --> 00:13:21,622
Many, many years ago,
the elders said that she's on a mission...

215
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:23,759
a mission to help others achieve things.

216
00:13:23,869 --> 00:13:26,497
And now she travels around helping-

217
00:13:26,605 --> 00:13:29,199
helping other creatures
who want something badly...

218
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:31,572
something very badly.

219
00:13:37,683 --> 00:13:42,347
- What's going on, Leader?
- There is something, something that haunts us.

220
00:13:42,454 --> 00:13:45,014
It's- It's something-

221
00:13:45,124 --> 00:13:48,616
A terrible creature from the depths.

222
00:13:48,727 --> 00:13:50,718
It's close to the reef.

223
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:56,163
[ Gasps ]
Huh?

224
00:13:56,268 --> 00:13:58,236
What's wrong, Sparky?

225
00:13:59,605 --> 00:14:02,403
Huh? Oh.

226
00:14:04,743 --> 00:14:06,973
There's something haunting us.

227
00:14:07,079 --> 00:14:09,343
Yeah. You know what, you're right.
And I feel the same.

228
00:14:09,448 --> 00:14:12,781
- It's getting closer. And even closer.
- [ Whimpers ]

229
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:17,245
It's horrible. It's almost here!
[ Gasps ]

230
00:14:18,290 --> 00:14:20,815
- Oh! [ Farts ]
- Oh! That's gross!

231
00:14:20,926 --> 00:14:23,394
You farted? Ew!

232
00:14:23,495 --> 00:14:26,521
- What was that?
- Ah! Mmm!

233
00:14:26,632 --> 00:14:28,532
Hmm? Huh?

234
00:14:28,634 --> 00:14:30,795
- Hey.
- [ Farts ] Oh, my!

235
00:14:30,903 --> 00:14:33,463
- What's happening?
- [ Giggles ] You're still farting.

236
00:14:33,572 --> 00:14:37,406
- Oh. Those are my friends. My stinky farts.
- What?

237
00:14:37,509 --> 00:14:39,477
If I can't hold them,
they escape without my permission.

238
00:14:39,578 --> 00:14:43,412
But they are my friends. Sometimes
when I need to breathe, I use them.

239
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:45,005
[ lnhales, Strains ]

240
00:14:45,117 --> 00:14:47,415
- [ Farting ]
- [ Gasping ]

241
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:48,952
[ Sniffs ]
See?

242
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:51,079
They come in handy
when you have to breathe.

243
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:54,250
And my star is mine.
Yes, my star is mine and only mine.

244
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:57,557
I'm sleepy.
[ Snoring ]

245
00:14:57,663 --> 00:14:59,130
Huh?

246
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:02,400
- [ Low Rumble ]
- Hmm?

247
00:15:02,501 --> 00:15:04,264
[ Hisses, Growls ]

248
00:15:05,304 --> 00:15:07,067
[ Gasps ]

249
00:15:08,841 --> 00:15:12,538
[ Daniel ]
Dream... or don't dream.

250
00:15:12,645 --> 00:15:15,944
Come... or don't.

251
00:15:22,888 --> 00:15:25,413
- Leader!
- What is wrong with you?

252
00:15:25,524 --> 00:15:27,458
You know it's bedtime.

253
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:30,892
- The rest of the pod is already asleep.
- I can't sleep.

254
00:15:30,996 --> 00:15:33,624
That's no reason
to hang out here all alone.

255
00:15:33,732 --> 00:15:36,599
Can I ask you something
about the sun?

256
00:15:36,702 --> 00:15:38,727
About the sun?

257
00:15:38,837 --> 00:15:41,465
Yes, the sun.
Does it ever look different?

258
00:15:41,573 --> 00:15:44,371
The sun is always the sun.

259
00:15:44,476 --> 00:15:47,309
It moves through the sky during the day,
if that's what you mean.

260
00:15:47,413 --> 00:15:49,108
No, no. Not that.

261
00:15:49,214 --> 00:15:51,876
Does it ever do anything strange?

262
00:15:51,984 --> 00:15:54,350
Anything that might be
out of the ordinary?

263
00:15:55,921 --> 00:16:01,154
- Why are you asking?
- Oh, just wondering. I guess I'm just curious.

264
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:05,321
I'd be happy if you just showed
this much interest when you're fishing.

265
00:16:05,431 --> 00:16:08,161
Sometimes I feel like
I'm not like the rest.

266
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:12,101
Nonsense. Come on.
It's time we get you back to bed.

267
00:16:12,204 --> 00:16:13,671
Let's go.

268
00:16:34,293 --> 00:16:36,659
[ Snoring ]
Don't eat my sea urchins!

269
00:16:36,762 --> 00:16:39,253
They're mine and only mine!

270
00:16:39,365 --> 00:16:41,629
[ Sighs, Snoring ]

271
00:16:41,734 --> 00:16:43,702
[ Gasps ]

272
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:50,903
[ Shudders ]

273
00:16:52,711 --> 00:16:53,678
Huh?

274
00:16:56,882 --> 00:16:58,349
[ Sighs ]

275
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:01,647
Huh?

276
00:17:01,754 --> 00:17:03,847
Ah!

277
00:17:03,956 --> 00:17:07,357
- [ Dolphins Snuffling ]
- [ Sighs ]

278
00:17:38,223 --> 00:17:39,690
[ Sighs ]

279
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:42,226
Maybe the leader really is right.

280
00:17:42,327 --> 00:17:44,989
[ Female Voice ]
There comes a time in life, Daniel...

281
00:17:45,097 --> 00:17:48,999
when there's nothing else to do
but to go your own way...

282
00:17:49,101 --> 00:17:52,070
a time to follow your dreams...

283
00:17:52,171 --> 00:17:55,902
a time to raise the sails
of your own beliefs.

284
00:17:56,008 --> 00:17:58,272
Who are you?
You're not the manta.

285
00:17:58,377 --> 00:18:01,676
- Your voice sounds different.
- I am the Voice of the Sea.

286
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:03,873
- The Voice of the Sea?
- Yes, Daniel.

287
00:18:03,982 --> 00:18:08,385
The manta that I sent to you in the lagoon
is one of my angels.

288
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:11,650
She told me about you.
You're ready.

289
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:13,384
Ready for what?

290
00:18:13,492 --> 00:18:17,428
Ready to take the great leap
into the unknown...

291
00:18:17,529 --> 00:18:20,259
far from the safety of the lagoon.

292
00:18:20,365 --> 00:18:23,095
What should I do?

293
00:18:23,202 --> 00:18:25,534
How will I know
the true purpose of my life?

294
00:18:26,705 --> 00:18:29,503
You will find the true
purpose ofyour life...

295
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:32,634
the day you surf the perfect wave...

296
00:18:32,744 --> 00:18:35,770
the one you've been
dreaming of for so long.

297
00:18:39,751 --> 00:18:41,048
- Daniel!
- [ Gasps ]

298
00:18:41,153 --> 00:18:42,643
Come back!

299
00:18:43,722 --> 00:18:47,488
- Uh-
- Daniel Alexander Dolphin!

300
00:18:47,593 --> 00:18:52,462
Come back immediately,
or you will regret it forever.

301
00:18:52,564 --> 00:18:55,124
[ Michael ]
Daniel, what are you doing?

302
00:18:55,234 --> 00:19:00,297
Daniel, this is the last time.
Come back, Daniel. Now!

303
00:19:00,405 --> 00:19:02,430
[ Groans ]

304
00:19:05,611 --> 00:19:07,977
I'm gonna miss you, Michael.

305
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,911
Daniel, no.

306
00:19:10,015 --> 00:19:11,949
Good-bye, Michael.

307
00:19:29,234 --> 00:19:31,202
Good-bye, Daniel.

308
00:19:32,471 --> 00:19:35,099
Now listen to me, everyone.

309
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:40,038
Today, one of us has broken the law.

310
00:19:41,647 --> 00:19:43,547
It was Daniel.

311
00:19:43,649 --> 00:19:46,209
Daniel chose to leave this pod.

312
00:19:46,318 --> 00:19:48,786
Daniel Alexander Dolphin...

313
00:19:48,887 --> 00:19:52,254
is now an outcast forever.

314
00:19:58,330 --> 00:20:00,798
[ Raspy Breathing ]

315
00:20:15,414 --> 00:20:19,145
[ Barracuda ]
The dreamer is finally out.

316
00:20:19,251 --> 00:20:21,515
[ Chortling ]

317
00:20:34,933 --> 00:20:36,901
[ Narrator ]
The next morning...

318
00:20:37,002 --> 00:20:42,372
Daniel Alexander Dolphin found himself
in the middle of a huge ocean...

319
00:20:42,474 --> 00:20:44,874
not knowing which way to go...

320
00:20:44,977 --> 00:20:47,241
but willing to follow
the voice of his heart.

321
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:52,739
[ Snuffling ]

322
00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:02,893
Ah.

323
00:21:20,178 --> 00:21:24,012
[ Creature Muttering ]
How'd I get stuck in the-

324
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,777
[ Whimpering ]
I just wanna-

325
00:21:25,884 --> 00:21:26,851
Huh?

326
00:21:26,952 --> 00:21:30,115
[ Straining, Muttering ]

327
00:21:30,222 --> 00:21:32,053
- Ouch!
- Ah!

328
00:21:33,158 --> 00:21:36,321
[ Straining, Whimpering ]

329
00:21:36,428 --> 00:21:39,795
I gotta get outta here!
[ Straining ]

330
00:21:39,898 --> 00:21:42,890
[ M uttering ]
Oh, gosh!

331
00:21:43,001 --> 00:21:45,697
How do I get myself
into these sort of things?

332
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:48,068
[ Grunts ]
You mind helping me out over here?

333
00:21:48,173 --> 00:21:49,640
Sure. I'll try.

334
00:21:49,741 --> 00:21:52,938
Ouch! Ow! Stop!

335
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:55,980
[ Panting ]
Stop it!

336
00:21:56,081 --> 00:21:58,447
Ouch! Be careful!

337
00:21:58,550 --> 00:22:00,108
You're ripping my guts out!

338
00:22:00,218 --> 00:22:03,676
[ Yelping ]
Whoa-oah-oah!

339
00:22:03,789 --> 00:22:05,552
Well, thanks a lot.

340
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:08,956
Let me ask you somethin'. Um, do I look
like I'm made out of chewing gum?

341
00:22:09,061 --> 00:22:11,029
- [ Squeaks ]
- Sorry..

342
00:22:11,129 --> 00:22:12,824
Eh!

343
00:22:12,931 --> 00:22:14,956
Hey, wait a minute.

344
00:22:16,702 --> 00:22:18,465
Where did you disappear to?

345
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:20,595
You're not plannin'
on eating me, are ya?

346
00:22:20,706 --> 00:22:22,298
No.

347
00:22:22,407 --> 00:22:25,376
Are you really, really for sure?

348
00:22:25,477 --> 00:22:27,638
Because I am superdelicious.

349
00:22:27,746 --> 00:22:31,477
- Of course not. I swear.
- Ooh! That's good news.

350
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:33,983
Ta-da!
[ Laughs ]

351
00:22:35,587 --> 00:22:38,954
Hey, hey! Close your mouth.
I can see all the way into your stomach.

352
00:22:39,057 --> 00:22:43,289
Hey. I- How did you do that?
Suddenly I couldn't see you.

353
00:22:43,395 --> 00:22:45,989
Eh, I did it the way I did it.

354
00:22:46,098 --> 00:22:47,793
That's me.

355
00:22:47,899 --> 00:22:50,060
And you, who are you?

356
00:22:50,168 --> 00:22:52,068
I'm Daniel Alexander Dolphin.

357
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:55,162
Ah. And what are you doin' here?

358
00:22:55,273 --> 00:23:00,370
See, well, I wanted to get out of my lagoon
and into the open ocean.

359
00:23:00,479 --> 00:23:04,210
- You ran away without permission?
- Yes. That's right.

360
00:23:04,316 --> 00:23:06,147
And now I'll never be able to go back.

361
00:23:06,251 --> 00:23:08,344
No!

362
00:23:08,453 --> 00:23:11,650
Daniel, I ran away too!

363
00:23:11,757 --> 00:23:16,251
That's right. Not because I was
lookin' for something, well, like you.

364
00:23:16,361 --> 00:23:17,760
I was just bored.

365
00:23:17,863 --> 00:23:21,390
A guy like me needs adventure,
needs to see the world.

366
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,832
I couldn't stay at home alone
with Ma forever, you know?

367
00:23:23,935 --> 00:23:26,597
It's just, um- Oh, it's a bit, uh-

368
00:23:26,705 --> 00:23:28,832
What's the word? D'oh!

369
00:23:28,940 --> 00:23:30,567
I got it! Oh, it's-
[ Jabbering ]

370
00:23:30,675 --> 00:23:32,768
Wait! I know this!
It's on the tip of my tongue!

371
00:23:32,878 --> 00:23:35,847
Uh, uh- Suffocatin'!
Yeah, suffocatin'. Know what I mean?

372
00:23:35,947 --> 00:23:38,177
Yes. I understand.

373
00:23:38,283 --> 00:23:40,843
[ Female, ltalian Accent ]
Carl! Carl, where are you?

374
00:23:40,952 --> 00:23:43,512
Stop hiding and come here right now!

375
00:23:43,622 --> 00:23:46,147
It's my mommy!
Oh, no! No, no, no, no!

376
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:49,159
Let's get outta here,
or I 'm gonna have to eat sea urchin again.

377
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,354
Have you ever had it, Daniel?
I don't like it!

378
00:23:51,463 --> 00:23:53,727
I don't like it! It itches!
I don't like it!

379
00:23:53,832 --> 00:23:55,891
Okay. Let's go.

380
00:23:56,001 --> 00:24:00,097
Whoa-oh!
[ Murmurs ]

381
00:24:00,205 --> 00:24:02,673
[ Straining, Panting ]

382
00:24:04,376 --> 00:24:06,844
[ Straining, Panting ]

383
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:11,806
[ Sighs ]
Wow.

384
00:24:11,917 --> 00:24:13,475
Carl, you're really fast.

385
00:24:13,585 --> 00:24:15,780
Hey, hurry up!
I'm leavin' you behind.

386
00:24:15,887 --> 00:24:18,447
Hey, uh, why don't you
grab on to my tail?

387
00:24:18,557 --> 00:24:20,889
[ Pants ]
Okay.

388
00:24:20,992 --> 00:24:23,586
But only because I don't want
to leave you behind.

389
00:24:23,695 --> 00:24:26,459
Gee, thanks a lot, Carl.

390
00:24:26,565 --> 00:24:28,590
[ Sighs ]

391
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:30,930
[ Yelping ]

392
00:24:31,036 --> 00:24:33,095
[ Shrieking ]

393
00:24:38,109 --> 00:24:41,101
[ Whimpering ]

394
00:24:41,213 --> 00:24:43,647
- Stop it!
- Uh, uh- Oh!

395
00:24:43,748 --> 00:24:45,978
- [ Screams ]
- [ Splats ]

396
00:24:46,084 --> 00:24:48,279
Whoops.

397
00:24:48,386 --> 00:24:50,877
Carl? Uh-

398
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:53,116
[ Groans ]

399
00:24:53,225 --> 00:24:54,351
Right here.

400
00:24:54,459 --> 00:24:56,427
Just makin' myself comfortable.

401
00:24:56,528 --> 00:24:58,428
[ Whimpers ]

402
00:24:58,530 --> 00:25:02,728
I think that we are... safe.

403
00:25:02,834 --> 00:25:05,394
Right? Heh, heh.
[ Groans ]

404
00:25:06,638 --> 00:25:09,698
I think that you have
to hold on to me tighter.

405
00:25:09,808 --> 00:25:13,244
What about on my back
just in front of my dorsal fin?

406
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:16,109
Hold on like this? That feels better.

407
00:25:16,214 --> 00:25:18,682
So, where we goin' now?
We off to have more fun?

408
00:25:18,783 --> 00:25:22,116
First, I've gotta swim to the surface
so I can get some air.

409
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:27,191
Ah!

410
00:25:27,292 --> 00:25:30,557
[ Carl Whimpering ]

411
00:25:31,730 --> 00:25:34,858
Wow. Carl, look at that.

412
00:25:34,966 --> 00:25:36,729
Surfing is the reason I live.

413
00:25:36,835 --> 00:25:39,736
[ Gasping ]

414
00:25:39,838 --> 00:25:42,739
- [ Panting ]
- Have you ever wanted to surf?

415
00:25:42,841 --> 00:25:47,369
Of course I have, Daniel,
but surfin' is too wild for me, you know.

416
00:25:47,479 --> 00:25:49,606
I prefer to be a little more relaxed...

417
00:25:49,714 --> 00:25:52,410
chilled out nice and smooth.

418
00:25:52,517 --> 00:25:54,485
So why'd you run away
from your lagoon?

419
00:25:54,586 --> 00:25:57,054
The lagoon where I live is beautiful...

420
00:25:57,155 --> 00:25:58,645
but it felt like a prison.

421
00:25:58,757 --> 00:26:00,657
Heh! Guess I'll come with you then.

422
00:26:00,759 --> 00:26:02,886
You can be my sidekick, okay?

423
00:26:02,994 --> 00:26:05,360
Carl, that sounds like
a pretty good plan to me.

424
00:26:05,463 --> 00:26:06,930
[ Water Rushing ]

425
00:26:07,032 --> 00:26:09,057
- [ Gasps ] Did you hear that?
- Yes.

426
00:26:09,167 --> 00:26:12,728
- [ Low Growl ]
- [ Yelps ] Mommy!

427
00:26:12,837 --> 00:26:14,964
- [ Whimpering ]
- [ Gasps ]

428
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:17,507
[ Growling ]

429
00:26:17,609 --> 00:26:19,600
Oh! Aah!

430
00:26:19,711 --> 00:26:22,544
[ Shrieking ]

431
00:26:22,647 --> 00:26:24,274
What do you want?

432
00:26:24,382 --> 00:26:27,783
[ Creature ]
Mmm, what do we want?

433
00:26:29,354 --> 00:26:33,017
Mmm, it could be your dorsal fin.

434
00:26:33,124 --> 00:26:36,787
Or maybe three delicious tentacles
from your brave friend.

435
00:26:36,895 --> 00:26:37,623
What?

436
00:26:37,729 --> 00:26:41,062
Or maybe just your dreams.

437
00:26:41,166 --> 00:26:42,690
Go away!

438
00:26:42,801 --> 00:26:45,634
[ Chuckles ]
There 's no reason to be scared.

439
00:26:45,737 --> 00:26:47,796
I ' m not scared.

440
00:26:47,906 --> 00:26:49,533
Wonderful.

441
00:26:49,641 --> 00:26:52,735
That way, it is easier to devour you.

442
00:26:52,844 --> 00:26:55,904
What? You? And how many more?

443
00:26:56,014 --> 00:26:57,447
[ Barracudas M uttering ]

444
00:26:57,549 --> 00:27:01,781
Oh. That wasn't a very smart question.

445
00:27:01,886 --> 00:27:04,753
[ Muttering Continues ]

446
00:27:18,837 --> 00:27:20,498
[ Gasps ]

447
00:27:22,674 --> 00:27:23,299
Aah!

448
00:27:24,876 --> 00:27:26,104
What are you?

449
00:27:26,211 --> 00:27:29,977
I am your worst nightmare.

450
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:31,946
[ Roaring ]

451
00:27:33,118 --> 00:27:35,211
Get them!
[ Growls ]

452
00:27:36,354 --> 00:27:38,822
[ Creature Chortling ]

453
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:52,064
[ Gasping ]

454
00:27:52,170 --> 00:27:54,195
[ Exhales ]

455
00:27:54,305 --> 00:27:56,205
Huh?
[ Sighs ]

456
00:28:02,881 --> 00:28:05,714
- [ Carl Whimpers ] Mommy.
- Hmm?

457
00:28:05,817 --> 00:28:08,047
Mommy. Mommy.

458
00:28:08,153 --> 00:28:11,816
No, I don't wanna eat any more jellyfish.

459
00:28:11,923 --> 00:28:13,686
[ Whimpering ]

460
00:28:13,792 --> 00:28:18,286
Oh, no! Jellyfish are terrible.
They're so gross.

461
00:28:18,396 --> 00:28:21,797
They make my belly itch.
[ Whimpering ]

462
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:24,562
[ Gasping ]

463
00:28:24,669 --> 00:28:26,569
[ Daniel ]
I think we lost them.

464
00:28:26,671 --> 00:28:29,663
Huh? What? Did I miss somethin'?

465
00:28:29,774 --> 00:28:31,639
Well- What, you don't remember?

466
00:28:31,743 --> 00:28:34,371
Oh. Last thing I remember,
I was eatin' a jellyfish.

467
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:36,709
Gross. Pfft! Gross. Yech!

468
00:28:36,815 --> 00:28:39,841
Jellyfish? Are there any
jellyfish that taste good?

469
00:28:39,951 --> 00:28:43,011
Nope. But they are good
for your digestion.

470
00:28:43,121 --> 00:28:45,885
[ Gasps ]
I remember!

471
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:51,087
I remember I was dreaming that
a thousand barracudas wanted to eat us...

472
00:28:51,196 --> 00:28:54,495
and I was bravely fighting them all!

473
00:28:54,599 --> 00:28:58,228
And I chased them away
with their tails between their legs! Ha!

474
00:28:58,336 --> 00:29:01,533
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.
That's exactly what you were doing.

475
00:29:01,639 --> 00:29:03,106
Of course.

476
00:29:03,208 --> 00:29:07,042
Because nobody messes
with the mighty Carl!

477
00:29:07,145 --> 00:29:09,010
Nobody!

478
00:29:09,114 --> 00:29:12,572
[ Screaming ]

479
00:29:14,552 --> 00:29:16,417
[ Roars ]

480
00:29:19,991 --> 00:29:22,619
[ Daniel Panting, Gasping ]

481
00:29:35,507 --> 00:29:37,805
[ Panting ]

482
00:29:44,816 --> 00:29:47,944
[ Creature Growling ]

483
00:29:53,024 --> 00:29:56,482
[ Daniel Gasping, Grunting ]

484
00:30:19,017 --> 00:30:20,814
[ Creature Groans ]

485
00:30:26,357 --> 00:30:28,587
[ Exhales ]

486
00:30:31,729 --> 00:30:33,424
- [ Chortling ]
- Huh?

487
00:30:43,107 --> 00:30:46,372
[ Whimpering ]

488
00:30:49,147 --> 00:30:51,672
- [ Growling ]
- We're goin' fast.

489
00:30:51,783 --> 00:30:55,514
[ Screams ]

490
00:31:11,669 --> 00:31:13,796
[ Panting ]

491
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:18,904
[ Gasping ]

492
00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:20,978
[ Growling ]

493
00:31:21,079 --> 00:31:23,138
[ Chortling ]

494
00:31:25,683 --> 00:31:28,413
[ Panting ]

495
00:31:30,255 --> 00:31:33,156
[ Breathing Slows ]

496
00:31:35,159 --> 00:31:37,093
No! It can't be.

497
00:31:37,195 --> 00:31:38,526
There's no way out!

498
00:31:38,630 --> 00:31:40,530
[ Creature ]
Are you trapped?

499
00:31:40,632 --> 00:31:43,328
[ Laughing ]

500
00:31:43,434 --> 00:31:45,902
I am going to enjoy this so much.

