to discover the truth with your own eyes.

748
00:47:26,810 --> 00:47:29,074
Yeah, I guess you're right, Daniel.

749
00:47:29,179 --> 00:47:31,443
Okay! Let's continue our adventure!

750
00:47:31,548 --> 00:47:34,278
- That's the spirit.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah! Whoo!

751
00:47:34,384 --> 00:47:36,784
[ Both Laughing ]

752
00:47:38,722 --> 00:47:41,520
Stop it. [ Chuckles ]
Stop!

753
00:47:41,625 --> 00:47:43,820
- Stop what?
- [ Chuckling Continues ]

754
00:47:43,927 --> 00:47:45,394
Huh?

755
00:47:47,331 --> 00:47:49,390
[ Muttering ]

756
00:47:49,499 --> 00:47:52,059
- [ Giggling, Squeaking ]
- Hmm.

757
00:47:53,103 --> 00:47:55,162
[ Murmurs ]

758
00:47:56,573 --> 00:47:58,473
[ Gasps, Laughs ]

759
00:47:58,575 --> 00:48:01,567
- Hey! Huh?
- Oh!

760
00:48:01,678 --> 00:48:05,045
Seems as if you're carrying
a stowaway, Daniel. Ha!

761
00:48:05,148 --> 00:48:07,173
Where do you come from, little fish?

762
00:48:07,284 --> 00:48:09,252
- Um-
- Can he talk?

763
00:48:09,353 --> 00:48:12,015
- Can you speak?
- Of course I can talk. [ Squeaking ]

764
00:48:12,122 --> 00:48:14,386
I can even count up to eight. Wanna see?

765
00:48:14,491 --> 00:48:18,018
- Sure!
- Oh, such a tiny thing. [ Gasps ]

766
00:48:18,128 --> 00:48:23,122
1, 3, 76, 41, 1 2-

767
00:48:23,233 --> 00:48:24,757
Um, 8!

768
00:48:24,868 --> 00:48:28,599
I can't take it! Oh, you're so cute!

769
00:48:28,705 --> 00:48:31,196
You're so cute, I could just-

770
00:48:31,308 --> 00:48:32,832
I could eat you!

771
00:48:32,943 --> 00:48:36,106
[ Gasps ]
No, Mr. Squid!

772
00:48:36,213 --> 00:48:38,010
Please don't eat me.
[ Squeaks ]

773
00:48:38,115 --> 00:48:41,016
Mr. Big Fish,
you won't let him eat me, will you?

774
00:48:41,118 --> 00:48:44,519
No, little buddy. Nobody's gonna eat you.
It was just a joke.

775
00:48:44,621 --> 00:48:47,681
Oh, yes, little fish,
I could never eat you.

776
00:48:47,791 --> 00:48:49,349
- Joke?
- [ Carl ] Uh-huh.

777
00:48:49,459 --> 00:48:51,518
I love funny jokes.
Very funny jokes!

778
00:48:51,628 --> 00:48:54,392
- You are adorable!
- [ Grunting ]

779
00:48:54,498 --> 00:48:56,329
I wanna keep him.
I always wanted a pet.

780
00:48:56,433 --> 00:48:57,798
[ Slurping ]

781
00:48:57,901 --> 00:49:00,233
- Why, you little devil!
- [ Giggling ]

782
00:49:00,337 --> 00:49:03,306
That's a bad boy!
Don't do that to your friend Carl!

783
00:49:03,407 --> 00:49:05,068
[ Whimpering ]

784
00:49:05,175 --> 00:49:07,109
Oh, no!

785
00:49:07,210 --> 00:49:10,111
Oh, little fishy,
don't look at me with that face!

786
00:49:10,213 --> 00:49:13,649
You can do whatever you want. Okay?
Huh, my little guy?

787
00:49:13,750 --> 00:49:15,445
[ Sighs, Giggles ]

788
00:49:15,552 --> 00:49:18,544
- Son!
- [ Gasps ] Mommy? Mommy!

789
00:49:18,655 --> 00:49:20,452
- Mommy!
- My little child.

790
00:49:20,557 --> 00:49:23,390
I've missed you so much.
[ Sighs ]

791
00:49:23,493 --> 00:49:24,983
I missed you too, Mommy.

792
00:49:25,095 --> 00:49:27,928
Thank you for freeing him
from that horrible prison.

793
00:49:28,832 --> 00:49:30,629
I have something to do, Carl.

794
00:49:30,734 --> 00:49:32,634
- Stay here.
- Wh-What are you doing?

795
00:49:32,736 --> 00:49:34,169
But, Daniel-

796
00:49:46,783 --> 00:49:49,843
- [ Loud Crash ]
- [ Gasping ]

797
00:49:49,953 --> 00:49:52,183
[ Grunting ]

798
00:49:52,289 --> 00:49:55,690
[ Gasping, Chattering ]

799
00:49:55,792 --> 00:49:58,158
[ Grunting Continues ]

800
00:49:58,261 --> 00:50:00,855
[ Creaking, Cracking ]

801
00:50:18,148 --> 00:50:21,845
- Get out! Now!
- [ Cheering, Shouting ]

802
00:50:21,952 --> 00:50:25,319
[ Laughing, Sighing ]

803
00:50:30,293 --> 00:50:33,160
- [ Maitre ] You!
- [ Grumbling ]

804
00:50:33,263 --> 00:50:36,892
Not only have you left without paying...

805
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,662
but now you want to steal my slaves!

806
00:50:39,770 --> 00:50:41,328
How dare you!

807
00:50:41,438 --> 00:50:44,635
How dare you make slaves
out of all of these innocent creatures?

808
00:50:44,741 --> 00:50:46,800
They're mine! They're mine!

809
00:50:46,910 --> 00:50:49,640
They're mine!

810
00:50:49,746 --> 00:50:53,409
They were never yours! You can't realize
your dreams by stealing the dreams of others.

811
00:50:53,517 --> 00:50:56,486
[ Yelling ]

812
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:11,267
Carl?

813
00:51:12,302 --> 00:51:14,031
- [ Carl Chattering ]
- Huh?

814
00:51:14,137 --> 00:51:16,037
[ Chattering Continues ]

815
00:51:16,139 --> 00:51:19,575
Yes. Yes, right here. I got you.
You get away from me!

816
00:51:19,676 --> 00:51:22,770
- [ Chuckles ]
- Wait till my friend Daniel gets here!

817
00:51:22,879 --> 00:51:25,211
- He's gonna- [ Gasps ]
- What's wrong, Carl?

818
00:51:25,315 --> 00:51:27,374
Look!
[ Shuddering ]

819
00:51:27,484 --> 00:51:30,112
- [ Gasps ]
- How nice! Another visitor!

820
00:51:30,220 --> 00:51:33,121
Your friend here
doesn't wanna talk to me.

821
00:51:33,223 --> 00:51:36,420
He's trying to poke me
with this pointy thing.

822
00:51:36,526 --> 00:51:40,121
Stay back! A sea urchin in my hands
is a deadly weapon!

823
00:51:40,230 --> 00:51:42,357
- [ Squealing ]
- Hyah! Hi-yah!

824
00:51:42,466 --> 00:51:43,899
What do you want?

825
00:51:44,000 --> 00:51:47,458
First I'd like to find out who I have
the pleasure of meeting here.

826
00:51:47,571 --> 00:51:50,540
- [ Whimpering ]
- [ Squealing Continues ]

827
00:51:54,978 --> 00:51:57,412
I hope you can, uh, stay to eat.

828
00:51:57,514 --> 00:52:00,745
- [ Chuckles ] l- I mean, to talk.
- We're only passing by.

829
00:52:00,851 --> 00:52:03,615
"Passing by." lnteresting.

830
00:52:03,720 --> 00:52:07,383
-Well, aren't you scared of me?
-I don't fear what I don't know.

831
00:52:07,491 --> 00:52:10,619
Well, y-you should be careful
out here in the open ocean.

832
00:52:11,995 --> 00:52:13,895
A-And where's the rest of your pod?

833
00:52:13,997 --> 00:52:16,056
They must be fishing
in the island's lagoon.

834
00:52:16,166 --> 00:52:19,329
- So what are you doing out here all alone?
- I'm following my dream.

835
00:52:19,436 --> 00:52:22,234
- I'm looking for the perfect wave.
- Blah, blah, blah.

836
00:52:22,339 --> 00:52:25,137
Now just a second here.
What kind of a dream is that?

837
00:52:25,242 --> 00:52:28,803
Isn't there anything you want
with all of your heart?

838
00:52:28,912 --> 00:52:31,972
Me? I- I don't know.

839
00:52:32,082 --> 00:52:34,983
Come on. We all want something.

840
00:52:35,085 --> 00:52:40,648
But most creatures get so busy that they
lose track of their true purpose in life.

841
00:52:40,757 --> 00:52:42,190
Ya think so?

842
00:52:42,292 --> 00:52:43,884
Of course.

843
00:52:43,994 --> 00:52:46,326
Even my friend Carl here has a wish...

844
00:52:46,429 --> 00:52:48,090
but he doesn't know what it is yet.

845
00:52:48,198 --> 00:52:50,189
- That's why we travel together.
- But-

846
00:52:50,300 --> 00:52:53,463
- You know what I'm talking about, don't you?
- Of course.

847
00:52:53,570 --> 00:52:56,596
Yes, I think so.
At least that's what I'd like to think.

848
00:52:56,706 --> 00:52:59,197
You don't happen to know where
I could find the perfect wave.

849
00:52:59,309 --> 00:53:00,970
I bet you get around, don't you?

850
00:53:01,077 --> 00:53:05,070
Well, you know,
I myself, I'm not so interested in waves.

851
00:53:05,182 --> 00:53:07,650
- That's simply not my thing.
- Sure.

852
00:53:07,751 --> 00:53:10,049
Not everybody likes the same thing.

853
00:53:10,153 --> 00:53:11,552
That'd be pretty boring.

854
00:53:11,655 --> 00:53:13,486
Exactly. Exactly!

855
00:53:13,590 --> 00:53:16,855
So, what is it you really wish?

856
00:53:16,960 --> 00:53:19,861
My- M-M-My wish?

857
00:53:19,963 --> 00:53:23,091
Well, I don't, uh-

858
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:26,966
I don't, uh- Well,
you know what I am, right?

859
00:53:27,070 --> 00:53:30,164
Of course. Naturally. A shark.

860
00:53:30,273 --> 00:53:32,434
A shark? Ha!

861
00:53:32,542 --> 00:53:36,103
You obviously don't know
who you're dealing with here.

862
00:53:36,213 --> 00:53:38,738
They know me from here to Zanzibar.

863
00:53:38,848 --> 00:53:42,215
I mean, I'm the biggest,
the meanest and, uh-

864
00:53:42,319 --> 00:53:44,048
[ Chuckles ]

865
00:53:44,154 --> 00:53:46,714
You know what they say about me...

866
00:53:46,823 --> 00:53:48,347
don't ya?

867
00:53:48,458 --> 00:53:51,518
Yeah, yeah, the usual talk-

868
00:53:51,628 --> 00:53:55,257
That you eat a lot and everyone's
really scared of you, stuff like that.

869
00:53:55,365 --> 00:53:58,664
- But you see, that's the whole problem here.
- What?

870
00:53:58,768 --> 00:54:01,896
Everyone's afraid of me
and runs away when they see me...

871
00:54:02,005 --> 00:54:04,496
and it's so impossible
for me to talk to them.

872
00:54:04,608 --> 00:54:06,701
So you want to have friends to talk to?

873
00:54:06,810 --> 00:54:12,578
How can I talk to anybody if, before they say
anything, I'm already chompin' them down?

874
00:54:12,682 --> 00:54:14,912
- [ Muttering ]
- Well, that is a real problem.

875
00:54:15,018 --> 00:54:16,918
But nothing that can't be solved.

876
00:54:17,020 --> 00:54:21,821
Think. Everybody runs away
because you try and eat them.

877
00:54:21,925 --> 00:54:23,586
So then-

878
00:54:23,693 --> 00:54:26,127
I eat them before they go away.

879
00:54:26,229 --> 00:54:30,222
No! If you don't eat them,
then you can talk to them.

880
00:54:30,333 --> 00:54:32,426
Easy, don't you think?

881
00:54:32,535 --> 00:54:35,902
If I don't eat them, I can talk to them...

882
00:54:36,006 --> 00:54:38,702
and they can talk to me.

883
00:54:38,808 --> 00:54:40,605
Of course!

884
00:54:40,710 --> 00:54:44,737
That's why when I eat them
they don't talk!

885
00:54:44,848 --> 00:54:46,543
Well, some scream.

886
00:54:46,650 --> 00:54:49,141
- But screaming's not talking.
- [ All Yelling ]

887
00:54:49,252 --> 00:54:50,947
Cool, huh?

888
00:54:51,054 --> 00:54:53,215
Well, I have to try. it.

889
00:54:53,323 --> 00:54:56,258
- Where are the fish?
- Take it easy, my friend.

890
00:54:56,359 --> 00:54:59,055
- You just called me "friend"?
- Yeah. Why?

891
00:54:59,162 --> 00:55:01,392
Nobody has ever called me his friend.

892
00:55:01,498 --> 00:55:03,363
Sure feels good, right?

893
00:55:04,067 --> 00:55:07,002
[ Shrieking, Panting ]

894
00:55:07,103 --> 00:55:10,266
- [ Laughs ]
- Hey, what did you do that for?

895
00:55:10,373 --> 00:55:11,897
Carl's my friend.

896
00:55:12,008 --> 00:55:13,566
Sorry, sorry.

897
00:55:13,677 --> 00:55:15,736
I wanted to not eat you.

898
00:55:15,845 --> 00:55:20,179
I just have to practice this
a little more until I get it right.

899
00:55:20,283 --> 00:55:22,513
I'm really sorry, little guy.

900
00:55:22,619 --> 00:55:25,110
I almost messed up, didn't l?

901
00:55:25,221 --> 00:55:28,782
I've just never done this before,
this whole not-eating thing.

902
00:55:28,892 --> 00:55:32,020
Uh, it's okay. You'll learn how.

903
00:55:32,128 --> 00:55:34,926
Well, thankyou, my friends.

904
00:55:35,031 --> 00:55:37,932
Hey! You there!
Wait a second, fishies!

905
00:55:38,034 --> 00:55:41,094
I'll get you guys anyway,
but I won't eat you.

906
00:55:41,204 --> 00:55:44,605
Do you hear me?
You'd better wait for me!

907
00:55:46,209 --> 00:55:48,302
[ Whimpering ]

908
00:55:48,411 --> 00:55:51,039
- [ Shark ] Ohh! Come on! It was just a fin!
- [ Gasping ]

909
00:55:51,147 --> 00:55:55,015
- [ Screaming ]
- Don't go away! I won't do it again!

910
00:55:55,118 --> 00:55:56,881
Let's get outta here!

911
00:55:56,986 --> 00:56:00,012
- Did you see that, Carl?
- Yeah, yeah. Whatever you say!

912
00:56:00,123 --> 00:56:03,752
Look, let's just get outta here
before he changes his mind!

913
00:56:26,082 --> 00:56:29,176
[ Coughing ]

914
00:56:30,587 --> 00:56:33,249
That dolphin made the worst mistake...

915
00:56:33,356 --> 00:56:36,189
of his miserable existence.

916
00:56:36,292 --> 00:56:39,261
[ Growling ]

917
00:56:53,910 --> 00:56:55,605
[ Carl, Daniel Laughing ]

918
00:56:55,712 --> 00:56:59,341
[ Carl ] First, I gave a lesson to a shark
that likes biting his friends...

919
00:56:59,449 --> 00:57:03,283
and before that, I defeated
a monster full of scars...

920
00:57:03,386 --> 00:57:05,820
after defeating his army of barracudas.

921
00:57:05,922 --> 00:57:09,016
Ha! I can't wait
for the next challenge, Daniel.

922
00:57:09,125 --> 00:57:11,559
Lucius, the dream-eater.

923
00:57:11,661 --> 00:57:13,720
[ Yelps ]

924
00:57:14,664 --> 00:57:16,598
Lucius, the dream-eater?

925
00:57:16,699 --> 00:57:21,534
The creature that you described
is Lucius, the dream-eater.

926
00:57:21,638 --> 00:57:26,098
He lives to capture the dreams
of all creatures that inhabit the ocean.

927
00:57:26,209 --> 00:57:28,769
I'm surprised you survived
an encounter with him.

928
00:57:28,878 --> 00:57:31,278
I don't think he'll bother us anymore.

929
00:57:31,381 --> 00:57:35,875
I personally took care of the dream-eater
with my bare tentacles.

930
00:57:35,985 --> 00:57:38,977
Hoo! If that's so, then it's good news.

931
00:57:39,088 --> 00:57:41,750
- Who are you?
- I am a sunfish.

932
00:57:41,858 --> 00:57:45,726
And before you ask me what I'm doing,
I am swimming after the sun.

933
00:57:45,829 --> 00:57:48,798
- Hey, I like the sun!
- You like the sun?

934
00:57:48,898 --> 00:57:54,598
That's so cool. I've always fantasized
about touching the sun.

935
00:57:54,704 --> 00:57:56,501
If only for an instant.

936
00:57:56,606 --> 00:57:59,074
- You wanna touch it?
- As it gets close to the ocean.

937
00:57:59,175 --> 00:58:02,042
Imagine almost touching it
before it disappears.

938
00:58:02,145 --> 00:58:03,612
It could happen, right?

939
00:58:03,713 --> 00:58:06,739
If you think so.
But try not to burn yourself.

940
00:58:06,850 --> 00:58:09,182
My dream is to touch the sun.

941
00:58:09,285 --> 00:58:11,446
- I also have a dream.
- Really?

942
00:58:11,554 --> 00:58:14,580
I've been searching the sea
to find the perfect wave.

943
00:58:14,691 --> 00:58:18,252
Daniel... Alexander... Dolphin?

944
00:58:18,361 --> 00:58:21,330
- How do you know my name?
- So the story was true.

945
00:58:21,431 --> 00:58:23,922
- What story?
- Yeah, what story?

946
00:58:24,033 --> 00:58:27,059
Many suns ago, I heard
the story of a dolphin...

947
00:58:27,170 --> 00:58:31,266
that would break all the rules
of the society in which he lived...

948
00:58:31,374 --> 00:58:33,968
so that he could discover his destiny...

949
00:58:34,077 --> 00:58:37,843
and open the world of dreams
to all other creatures of the world.

950
00:58:37,947 --> 00:58:39,642
Who, me?

951
00:58:39,749 --> 00:58:41,478
Maybe you still don't know it, Daniel...

952
00:58:41,584 --> 00:58:44,610
but you were born to change the world...

953
00:58:44,721 --> 00:58:50,057
and one day you will return from where
you came after fulfilling your dreams...

954
00:58:50,159 --> 00:58:52,650
and will show them the truth.

955
00:58:52,762 --> 00:58:56,323
You mean, go back to my lagoon?
Back to my pod?

956
00:58:56,432 --> 00:58:59,526
Not a chance. I'll never go back.
They don't understand me.

957
00:58:59,636 --> 00:59:01,831
Don't be so harsh with them, Daniel.

958
00:59:01,938 --> 00:59:04,429
I wish you the best, Daniel.

959
00:59:04,541 --> 00:59:08,170
What you're searching for
is closer than you might think.

960
00:59:08,278 --> 00:59:10,644
Good-bye, Sunfish.

961
00:59:10,747 --> 00:59:14,205
And hopefully someday
you and I'll meet again.

962
00:59:23,893 --> 00:59:25,690
[ Moans ]

963
00:59:25,795 --> 00:59:28,127
[ Sinister Laugh ]

964
00:59:30,233 --> 00:59:31,791
[ Grunts ]

965
00:59:34,337 --> 00:59:36,601
[ Both Sighing ]

966
00:59:38,675 --> 00:59:40,575
Huh?

967
00:59:40,677 --> 00:59:42,668
What's the matter, Daniel?

968
00:59:42,779 --> 00:59:44,337
Are you sad?

969
00:59:44,447 --> 00:59:47,848
Forgive me, Carl, for bringing you
on this journey that has no meaning.

970
00:59:47,951 --> 00:59:50,419
I'm beginning to think I'll never
find what I'm searching for.

971
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:54,581
What am I hearing? The great dreamer
stopped dreaming just like that?

972
00:59:54,691 --> 00:59:58,855
What happened to your wave?
I think you're very close to finding it.

973
00:59:58,962 --> 01:00:01,226
- Huh?
- Sea?

974
01:00:02,865 --> 01:00:04,389
That dream is mine!

975
01:00:04,500 --> 01:00:07,060
- [ Both Gasping ]
- [ Roaring ]

976
01:00:09,138 --> 01:00:10,969
- [ Grunts ]
- Carl!

977
01:00:12,642 --> 01:00:14,269
No!

978
01:00:15,812 --> 01:00:18,406
[ Chuckles ]
Your turn, dreamer.

979
01:00:18,514 --> 01:00:22,109
- [ Barracudas Muttering ]
- That dreamer is mine.

980
01:00:23,152 --> 01:00:24,915
- Stay behind.
- [ Grunts ]

981
01:00:27,256 --> 01:00:29,781
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Yells ]

982
01:00:36,733 --> 01:00:39,395
[ Both Grunting, Yelling ]

983
01:00:51,681 --> 01:00:54,616
[ Roaring ]

984
01:01:14,570 --> 01:01:17,004
[ Roaring ]

985
01:01:30,553 --> 01:01:32,111
[ Groaning ]

986
01:01:33,990 --> 01:01:37,448
[ Growling ]

987
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:40,324
[ Grunting ]

988
01:01:42,231 --> 01:01:44,165
